                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/519: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia (<persName type="from"
                            >Skinner</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-18T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 18, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Tass in <hi rend="italic">Izvestia</hi> May 16th denies <hi rend="italic">New
                        York Times</hi> report May 14th from Washington concerning Trans-Siberian
                    Railway and troop concentrations. Soviets are not and do not intend transferring
                    troops to Eastern Siberia, are pursuing unswerving peace policy towards Japan
                    and Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
